---
import Shell from '../layouts/Shell.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---
<Shell
  title="Laser Studio · Photo to Laser File Software for Diode & CO2 — DigitalChiselCo"
  description="Laser Studio turns photos, STL 3D models and the real night sky into ready-to-burn laser files — 11 art styles, star maps, sundials, tumbler wraps and a full calibration suite. 100% offline, one-time purchase, works with LightBurn, xTool, Glowforge, LaserGRBL and RDWorks."
  scrollPastBanner={true}
>
  <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[{ label: 'Laser Studio' }]} />

  <article class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

    <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
    <header class="text-center mb-10">
      <p class="text-xs tracking-widest text-bronze-600 mb-3">★ NEW FROM DIGITALCHISELCO · DESKTOP SOFTWARE</p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl text-bronze-800 leading-tight">
        Laser <em class="italic text-bronze-600">Studio</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg md:text-xl text-ink-700/85 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        One app turns your photos, 3D models and even the night sky into ready-to-burn laser files —
        on your own computer, offline, forever.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
        <a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/DigitalChiselCo" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
           class="bg-bronze-600 text-cream px-7 py-3 rounded-md text-sm hover:bg-bronze-700 transition shadow">Get Laser Studio →</a>
        <a href="/contact" class="border border-bronze-600 text-bronze-700 px-7 py-3 rounded-md text-sm hover:bg-bronze-600/10 transition">Ask a question</a>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-ink-700/60">Windows 10/11 · one-time purchase · no subscription · nothing uploaded, ever</p>
    </header>

    <figure class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-bronze-600/25 shadow-lg mb-16">
      <img src="/laser-studio/app.jpg" alt="The Laser Studio workspace — a photo converted to a laser-ready 3D relief on the artboard" width="1400" height="787" loading="eager" class="w-full" />
      <figcaption class="text-center text-xs text-ink-700/60 py-2 bg-cream">The real Laser Studio workspace — five modes, one quiet artboard.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <!-- ===== WHY GAME CHANGER ===== -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl text-bronze-800 text-center">Why this is a game changer<br class="hidden md:block"/> for the laser market</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-ink-700/85 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Laser makers today juggle a photo-prep website, a dithering tool, a star-map generator, a box maker and a
        settings forum — plus a subscription or two. Laser Studio replaces the whole stack with one honest desktop app.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        <div class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-white">
          <p class="text-2xl">🎨</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-bronze-800 mt-2">Eleven products from one photo</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700/85">Engrave, 3D-illusion relief, pencil sketch, stipple, word portrait, spiral, string art, ASCII, low-poly, contour and a solvable maze — the same customer photo becomes eleven sellable product lines, each in seconds. No other tool on the market does this.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-white">
          <p class="text-2xl">🔒</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-bronze-800 mt-2">Offline. Owned. Private.</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700/85">While the industry moves to cloud subscriptions, Laser Studio runs 100% on your PC. Your customers' photos never leave your computer, there's no monthly fee, and it keeps working with or without the internet — buy once, use forever.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-white">
          <p class="text-2xl">🎯</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-bronze-800 mt-2">Measured settings, not guesses</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700/85">The #1 frustration in laser forums is "what power and speed do I use?" Laser Studio's calibration reads a photo of your own test burn and recommends YOUR machine's best setting — measured on your material, not copied from a stranger's post.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-white">
          <p class="text-2xl">🌌</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-bronze-800 mt-2">Whole product categories in a click</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700/85">Real star maps for any date and place, working sundials computed for your latitude, handwriting recipe boards, tumbler wraps at true circumference, press-fit boxes — each one a finished product a print-shop tool simply can't make.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-white">
          <p class="text-2xl">⚡</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-bronze-800 mt-2">Diode AND CO2, first-class</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700/85">Every export ships one organised ZIP: 1-bit dithers for diode lasers, hi-res grayscale and 16-bit depth for CO2/fibre/galvo, and real-millimetre SVG cut lines — with a read-me that says exactly which folder your laser needs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-white">
          <p class="text-2xl">🪪</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl text-bronze-800 mt-2">Built for sellers</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-700/85">Watermarked client proofs with scan-to-approve QR codes end spelling-mistake refunds. A time &amp; cost estimator prices every job. A project journal remembers every export. Care cards ship with every order.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== ELEVEN STYLES ===== -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-bronze-800 text-center">One photo. Eleven finished looks.</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ink-700/85 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Pick a style from one dropdown and its own sliders appear — every look below was generated from the same photograph.
      </p>
      <figure class="mt-8 rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-bronze-600/25 shadow">
        <img src="/laser-studio/styles.jpg" alt="Nine laser art styles generated from one photo: sketch, stipple, word portrait, spiral, string art, ASCII, low-poly, contour and maze" width="1200" height="1301" loading="lazy" class="w-full" />
      </figure>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-ink-700/70 text-center">
        Sketch · Stipple · Word Portrait · Spiral · String Art · ASCII · Low-Poly · Contour · Maze — plus the faithful photo engrave and the 3D-illusion relief.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== STL + STAR MAP split ===== -->
    <section class="mb-16 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-start">
      <div>
        <figure class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-bronze-600/25 shadow mb-4">
          <img src="/laser-studio/relief.jpg" alt="An STL 3D model converted into a hand-carved-looking laser relief engrave" width="1100" height="1093" loading="lazy" class="w-full" />
        </figure>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-bronze-800">Drop an STL. Get a carving.</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700/85 text-sm">
          The 3D-illusion engine relights any STL model as a hand-carved masterpiece — swing the light around it,
          dial the depth, boost the detail. Exports flat single-pass engraves for any laser <em>and</em> true 16-bit
          depth maps for real 3D carving. It pairs perfectly with our <a href="/catalog" class="text-bronze-600">1,200+ bas-relief STL files</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <figure class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-bronze-600/25 shadow mb-4">
          <img src="/laser-studio/starmap.jpg" alt="A heart-shaped star map of the real night sky with names in script" width="1000" height="1282" loading="lazy" class="w-full" />
        </figure>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-bronze-800">The sky, that night.</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700/85 text-sm">
          Astronomically real stars, the Moon at its true phase, the planets that were up — over any place and moment
          on Earth. Heart-shaped skies, "where we met" street-map combos, a song's soundwave ringing the sky with a
          QR that plays it. Engrave it, or print it in colour and frame it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== PRODUCT MAKERS ===== -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-bronze-800 text-center">Product makers, built in</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-5">
        <figure class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl overflow-hidden bg-white">
          <img src="/laser-studio/sundial.jpg" alt="A working sundial generated for a specific latitude" class="w-full" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption class="p-4"><strong class="text-bronze-800">A sundial that works.</strong><br/><span class="text-sm text-ink-700/80">Hour lines computed from real solar geometry for your latitude.</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl overflow-hidden bg-white">
          <img src="/laser-studio/recipe.jpg" alt="A recipe board composed from cleaned handwriting with a ruler edge" class="w-full" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption class="p-4"><strong class="text-bronze-800">Grandma's recipe, forever.</strong><br/><span class="text-sm text-ink-700/80">Photograph the card — the ink lifts clean off the paper.</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl overflow-hidden bg-white">
          <img src="/laser-studio/tumbler.jpg" alt="A tumbler wrap previewed on a 3D cup mockup" class="w-full" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption class="p-4"><strong class="text-bronze-800">Tumblers, done right.</strong><br/><span class="text-sm text-ink-700/80">True-circumference wraps with a spinnable 3D preview.</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="border border-bronze-600/25 rounded-xl overflow-hidden bg-white">
          <img src="/laser-studio/proof.jpg" alt="A watermarked client proof card with approval QR code" class="w-full" loading="lazy" />
          <figcaption class="p-4"><strong class="text-bronze-800">No more spelling refunds.</strong><br/><span class="text-sm text-ink-700/80">Watermarked client proofs with a scan-to-approve QR.</span></figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== COMPATIBILITY ===== -->
    <section class="mb-16 border border-bronze-600/30 rounded-xl p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-white">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-bronze-800 text-center">Works with the laser you already own</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-sm text-ink-700/85">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-bronze-700 mb-2">Machines</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5">
            <li>✓ Diode / blue-light — xTool D1, Ortur, Sculpfun, Atomstack &amp; similar</li>
            <li>✓ CO2 — K40, OMTech, Glowforge &amp; other CO2 machines</li>
            <li>✓ Fibre &amp; galvo markers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-bronze-700 mb-2">Software it feeds</p>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5">
            <li>✓ LightBurn — grayscale, dither &amp; 16-bit depth workflows</li>
            <li>✓ xTool Creative Space (XCS) · Glowforge app</li>
            <li>✓ LaserGRBL · RDWorks / LaserWORKS</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-5 text-xs text-ink-700/60 text-center">
        Laser Studio creates the design files; your laser software fires the beam. Power &amp; speed are dialled in with the
        built-in calibration tools on <em>your</em> machine and material — measured, never guessed.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== FACTS + CTA ===== -->
    <section class="mb-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-bronze-800">The plain facts</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose mt-5 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm max-w-2xl mx-auto text-left text-ink-700/85">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-bronze-600">✓</span> Windows 10 / 11 — installs in one click, no setup</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-bronze-600">✓</span> One-time purchase — no subscription, ever</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-bronze-600">✓</span> 100% offline — photos never leave your PC</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-bronze-600">✓</span> Illustrated Deluxe user manual included</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-bronze-600">✓</span> Every export sorted for diode, CO2 &amp; vector</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-bronze-600">✓</span> Made by the studio behind 1,200+ STL designs</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 mb-4 border border-bronze-600/30 rounded-xl p-8 text-center bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-white">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-bronze-800">Turn your next photo into a product tonight.</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-ink-700">Laser Studio is available now from our shop — and every DigitalChiselCo STL file works in it with zero conversion.</p>
      <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
        <a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/DigitalChiselCo" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="bg-bronze-600 text-cream px-6 py-3 rounded-md text-sm hover:bg-bronze-700 transition shadow">Get Laser Studio →</a>
        <a href="/catalog" class="border border-bronze-600 text-bronze-700 px-6 py-3 rounded-md text-sm hover:bg-bronze-600/10 transition">Browse STL designs for it</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Shell>
